```json
{
  "application": "mlflow",
  "software": [
    "SLURM",
    "OpenMPI",
    "Python 3.11.0",
    "Intel Compiler",
    "mlflow",
    "AMD EPYC 7763",
    "ConnectX-6",
    "A100"
  ],
  "resources": [
    "GPU",
    "CPU",
    "Memory",
    "Network"
  ],
  "environment": [
    "rhel8/default-icl",
    "python/3.11.0-icl",
    "venv"
  ],
  "dependencies": [
    "models.models1",
    "models.models1.FullyCNN",
    "models.models1.SoftPlusTransform",
    "models.models1.HeteroskedasticGaussianLossV2"
  ]
}
```

This script runs an MLflow application. It utilizes SLURM to manage its execution on a cluster with AMD EPYC 7763 CPUs, ConnectX-6 networking, and A100 GPUs.  The script configures and loads modules for Python 3.11.0 with Intel Compiler support. It also uses a virtual environment for the application.
